# 1 kubectl — Quick Notes 

What is kubectl?
kubectl = Command-line tool to talk to Kubernetes cluster. Type a command → it sends HTTP request to API Server → cluster acts on it.

# How it works from Laptop

kubectl get pods
     ↓
Reads ~/.kube/config        ← cluster address + your credentials
     ↓
Sends HTTPS request → API Server → etcd → returns result
     ↓
Output shows in Terminal

# kubeconfig-ல 3 things:

cluster — API server address
user — your certificate / token
context — which cluster + user + namespace to use

# How it works Inside a Pod (CI/CD)

GitLab / GitHub Actions Pod start ஆகுது
     ↓
ServiceAccount token auto-mount ஆகும்
/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token
     ↓
kubectl automatically reads it → no kubeconfig needed
     ↓
API Server → etcd → result

# Cost Tip

Inside Pod-ல SA-க்கு minimum permission மட்டும் கொடு. Overpowered SA → accidental delete → downtime → revenue loss.

bashkubectl auth can-i delete deployments --namespace=production    ## if answer NO means Safe

